# Copy to .env and set your key. Never commit .env.
#
# Local dev: `npm run dev` runs scripts/dev-server.cjs (static files + /api/weather like Vercel).
# Use `npm run serve:static` only if you do not need the weather proxy.
#
# GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY — required in the browser for Maps JavaScript + Directions (HTTP referrer
# restriction is OK: include http://127.0.0.1:*/* http://localhost:*/* and your deploy URL(s)).
#
# GOOGLE_MAPS_SERVER_KEY — optional but recommended for api/weather.js (local dev-server + Vercel).
# Use a second API key with Application restrictions: None (or IP if you prefer) and API
# restrictions limited to "Weather API" only. Reason: server-side requests do not send your
# site's HTTP Referer, so a referrer-only browser key often returns errors from the Weather API.
# If unset, the proxy falls back to GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY (works only if that key is not
# referrer-restricted for server use, or Google accepts it for your project).
#
# Required in Google Cloud (same or linked billing project as the keys):
#   - Maps JavaScript API
#   - Directions API (Legacy) — enable at:
#     https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/directions-backend.googleapis.com
#   - Weather API — enable at:
#     https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/weather.googleapis.com
#   - Billing on
#
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID — optional OAuth 2.0 Web application client id (ends in .apps.googleusercontent.com).
# Injected into google-maps-config.js as window.__GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID__ for Sign-In / token flows.
# Never commit GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET; it must not appear in browser bundles.
#
# Vercel: set GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY and GOOGLE_MAPS_SERVER_KEY (recommended) under
# Project → Settings → Environment Variables for Production and Preview.
# Add GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID there too if you use OAuth in the app.

GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_MAPS_SERVER_KEY=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
